verbose_text: In addition, preoperative serum CRP and SCC-Ag levels were significant predictors for survival, either combined (P < 0.001 for 5-year DFS and OS for both) or separately (P = 0.001 for 5-year DFS and OS for CRP and P = 0.001 and 0.003 for 5-year DFS and OS, respectively, for SCC-Ag; Supplementary Figures 1A and 1B).
